---
title: "transmit - Streams Price Transmission (Payment Abstraction V2)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_check_role: transmit(priceData) called via WorkflowRouter
    q_check_role --> q_decode: caller has PRICE_ADMIN_ROLE
    q_check_role --> q_revert_role: unauthorized
    q_revert_role --> [*]: revert Unauthorized
    q_decode --> q_iter: decode price reports from priceData
    q_iter --> q_validate: for report in priceReports
    q_validate --> q_check_feed: feedId matches configured dataStreamsFeedId
    q_check_feed --> q_check_stale: feed configured for asset
    q_check_feed --> q_skip: feed not configured (skip)
    q_check_stale --> q_check_price: report.timestamp within stalenessThreshold
    q_check_stale --> q_skip: price data stale
    q_check_price --> q_update: price > 0
    q_check_price --> q_skip: price is zero
    q_update --> q_next: store price with timestamp for asset
    q_skip --> q_next: skip this report
    q_next --> q_iter: more reports
    q_next --> [*]: no more reports

    note right of q_update
        INV-001: Streams prices take priority over Data Feeds when fresh
        INV-002: Contract falls back to Data Feeds if no fresh Streams price
        INV-003: Price staleness checked against configurable threshold per asset
        INV-004: dataStreamsFeedDecimals used to normalize price precision
    end note
